Claim ID:      NASA
Creation Date: 1995/07/24
Due Date:      2001/05/02

 Propelling and controlling an aircraft by the force of magnetic flux
 variations is feasible and will be applied on a NASA engineered space 
 shuttle by 5/2/2001. 'Yes' coupons pay $1, 'No' coupons pay $1
 otherwise.
 
 Johnathan

Claim ID:      NC50
Creation Date: 1997/09/25
Due Date:      2001/01/01

 The Network Computer, as proposed by Oracle Corp., Sun Microsystems,
 Inc., & IBM Corp. acheives 50% of total single-processor computing
 units shipped worldwide by January 1, 2001. By single-processor
 computing units, I mean NCs, PCs, Macs, as well as the Wintel NetPC.
 This does not include high-end RISC-based UNIX or NT workstations, or 
 SMP systems. Market share is counted in units shipped, and not
 revenues. Information on these matters is provided my many online
 resources including Gartner Group and IDC. 

Claim ID:      NG2K
Creation Date: 1995/07/25
Due Date:      2000/11/07

 Newt Gingrich files as a candidate for President of the United States 
 in the year 2000. Claim will be held as true if Gingrich files as a
 candidate with the Federal Election Commission or its successor
 organization. In the event the Federal Election Commission is
 abolished with no successor organization, a public announcement of
 intent to seek the nomination of a political party or run as an
 independent or third-party candidate will suffice.

Claim ID:      NIPC
Creation Date: 1995/02/05
Due Date:      2001/01/01

 Non-Intel CPU personal computer sales (number of units sold) will
 outnumber Intel based systems by the year 2000. Non-Intel CPUs are
 defined to be all non-Intel x86 compatible chips such as the AMD K5,
 as well as other devices such as the PowerPC, Alpha and so on.
 Systems based on non-x86 compatible Intel chips such as the
 hypothetical P7 will count as Intel-based systems. For purposes of
 this claim personal computers are defined as those running DOS, any
 Windows variant, any MacOS variant, or any OS/2 variant. Other
 operating systems will be admissable if they exceed 5% sales rate of
 the combined sales rate of the above operating systems for a one year 
 time period.

Claim ID:      NLud
Creation Date: 1995/07/04
Due Date:      2020/05/01

 
    Kirkpatrick Sale will win his bet with Kevin Kelly. See [1]Wired 3.06
    page 216. Mr. Kelly proposed the bet, saying, "I bet you $1000 that in
    the year 2020, we're not even close ot the kind of disaster you
    describe--a convergence of three disasters: global currency collapse,
    significant warfare between rich and poor, and environmental disasters
    of some significant size. We won't even be close." Each of the parties
    has written a check to the publisher they share, Bill Patrick at
    Addison Wesley.
 
 References
 
    1. http://wwww.wired.com/wired/3.06/features/saleskelly.html

Claim ID:      NT599
Creation Date: 1998/09/20
Due Date:      2000/01/07

 This claim will be judged TRUE if Microsoft releases an operating
 system with the name "Windows NT 5" (or similar spelling thereof), on 
 or before December 31, 1999. 
 
  Background: The successor to Windows NT 4, called "Windows NT 5",
 has been in beta for a while. Its release date has been slipping by
 relatively large amounts; its codebase is rumoured to be in the range 
 of 40 million lines of code, and Sun's CEO claimed that such a
 product was "unmanageable". 
 
  This claim is not about the capability of the system, which may or
 may not vary widely from current expectations, but about its name and 
 release date.

Claim ID:      NUKE
Creation Date: 1995/10/10
Due Date:      2010/01/01

 A nuclear weapon will be used(in other than a test capacity)
 somewhere in the world by 1/1/2010. This event will be acknowledged
 in major publications(i.e. The London Times, The Washington Post, The 
 London Economist).  Each Yes Coupon pays $1 within 1 months of the
 publication of the use of a nuclear weapon. No coupons pay $1 on Jan. 
 1, 2010 if no nuclear weapon has been used anywhere in the world
 between October 10,1995 and Jan. 1, 2010.

Claim ID:      Neut
Creation Date: 1994/11/07
Due Date:      TBD

 The rest mass of the electron neutrino is greater than 0.01 eV in
 ordinary space.

Claim ID:      NoKb
Creation Date: 1995/02/21
Due Date:      2015/01/01

 By the year 2015, keyboards will no longer be the predominant mode of 
 data entry in the computing world.

Claim ID:      NoWin
Creation Date: 1999/02/21
Due Date:      2005/08/03

 On July 6, 2005, at least one of the following companies (or its
 successor and assignee) will exist and sell microcomputers, but will
 not offer any operating system licensed from Microsoft pre-installed
 on any of their microcomputers: Dell Computer Corp., Hewlett-Packard, 
 Compaq Computer Corp., Gateway 2000 Inc.
 
 (If all of the four companies listed cease to exist by the above
 date, the claim will not be satisfied, even if Microsoft disappears.
 Otherwise, the claim would be satisfied if Microsoft no longer exists 
 or no longer sells operating systems.)

Claim ID:      NucW
Creation Date: 1995/11/06
Due Date:      2010/01/01

 This claim will be judged YES if at any time prior to 1/1/2010 at
 least one kilogram of nuclear waste has been stored for at least one
 year in the proposed high level nuclear waste storage site at Yucca
 Mountain, Nevada. This claim will be judged NO if the site is
 converted to low level nuclear waste storage only.

Claim ID:      NyBA
Creation Date: 1996/05/20
Due Date:      TBD

 In April, two regional baby bells, NYNEX and Bell Atlantic, annouced
 their intention to merge.  Under the proposed terms of the merger,
 stockholders of NYNEX will receive one share of the new company.
 Stockholders of Bell Atlantic will receive 1.302 shares of the new
 company.  Before this merger can proceed, it must be approved by the
 stock holders of the two companies.  It must also be approved by
 state regulators (in the states the company will serve) and by
 federal regulators.  This claim will be judged true if this merger
 succeeds.  This claim will be judged true when local phone service in 
 the regions currently served by Bell Atlantic and by NYNEX are served 
 by a single company.  This claim will be judged false:    1) NYNEX
 and Bell Atlantic decide to call off the merger.    2) NYNEX or Bell
 Atlantic shareholders reject the merger (however,       a change
 could be made in the stock-swap ratios given above       and this
 claim could still be true.)    3) The deal is not approved by state
 or federal regulators, and       no compromise is reached.    4)
 NYNEX and Bell Atlantic agree to a partial merger, without      
 fully joining their local phone service operations.

Claim ID:      OJpay
Creation Date: 1997/02/05
Due Date:      2000/01/01

 This claim proves true and returns $1 for each yes coupon (nothing
 for each no coupon) on the date it is publicly verified that at 
 least $1 million of the O.J. Simpson judgment has actually been paid  
 the plaintiffs. If the year 2000 arrives first, no coupons receive 
 $1, yes coupons nothing. A negotiated settlement that brings the
 plaintiffs at least $1 million before the year 2000 satisfies this
 claim.
 
 On 4 Feb 97 a jury found OJ Simpson responsible for the deaths of 
 Nicole Brown Simpson and Ron Goldman and awarded the plaintiffs 33.5
 million dollars in compensatory/punitive damages. OJ says the case
 isn"t over and can attempt to minimize or eliminate the amount  he
 might pay. This claim rides on the outcome.

Claim ID:      OJvn
Creation Date: 1995/10/10
Due Date:      2000/01/01

 By 1/1/2000 someone will have either a) been convicted of the
 slayings of Nicole Simpson and Ron Goldman. b) been declared by a
 court non-guilty by reason of insanity c) been indicted but died
 before being convicted or declared innocent in court. This person or
 persons will not have been acting in concert with O.J. Simpson. (O.J. 
 Simpson cannot be retried for this slaying so the conviction of any
 individual not connected to him will vindicate him). Each Yes Coupon
 pays $1 as soon any of the three conditions above occur. No coupons
 pay $1 on 1/1/2000 if none of the three conditions of this claim
 occur.

Claim ID:      OPNRes
Creation Date: 1996/10/14
Due Date:      2020/06/01

 There will be a proof showing the nonexistence of odd perfect numbers 
    or a proof showing the existence of an odd perfect number
 (including   but not limited to a demonstrated example of an odd
 perfect number) by six months before the judging date.  The
 proof/example shall appear in a reputable mathematical journal and
 have stood up to critical review for at least six months by the
 judging date.
 
 If odd perfect numbers are  shown to exist OR not exist, this claim
 shall be judged YES.  If the question remains unresolved (as defined
 above) this claim shall be judged NO.

Claim ID:      OPNX
Creation Date: 1998/03/12
Due Date:      2003/12/31

 Proof of the NON-existence of Odd Perfect Numbers discovered (a
 perfect number is one whose proper divisors sum to itself)

Claim ID:      OSbORC
Creation Date: 1998/12/07
Due Date:      2005/01/01

 By 2005/1/1 an Open Source Database will exist for which statistics
 published at http://www.tpc.org show that the published statistics
 for an Open Source database will exceed Oracle performance in the
 TPC-D benchmark for a database of 100 Gigabyte or larger in the
 majority of test results for which Oracle publishes TPC-D benchmark
 data( current at the time the Open Source Results are published in
 the same size category for which Oracle publishes data and running on 
 hardware which is identical to the hardware for which Oracle has
 published test results or upon hardware which in the judges opinion
 is demonstrably slower than the hardware for which Oracle has
 published results.) The Open Source product may run on a different
 operating system than the Oracle benchmark case to which it is
 compared. 
 
 
 
  If for some reason the organization at http://www.tpc.org ceases to
 publish performance statistics, the judge may substitute an another
 authoritative source. For purposes of this claim, an Open Source
 database is a product which is distributed in the form tested as
 described above according the the license guidelines described at
 http://www.opensource.org(the organization publishing this web page
 owns the trademark to the term Open Source). An example of an Open
 Source Database product can be found at: http://www.postgresql.com
 
 
 
 Background: The publishing of TPC-D statistics at www.tpc.org has
 been a major component of Oracle's marketing effort. Recently, Oracle 
 has obtained significant press by issuing a challenge by which Oracle 
 claims supremacy in VLDB performance in some specific areas over
 Microsoft SQL Server(see http://wwww.oracle.com/challenge).
 Traditionally, the strong suit of Microsoft SQL Server and Sybase has 
 been in the TPC-C performance statistics which measure OLTP
 performance. Oracle, Sybase and Microsoft are all members of the
 organization which publishes the web page at http://www.tpc.org

Claim ID:      OspX
Creation Date: 1995/10/08
Due Date:      2000/01/01

 This claim will be judged YES if the Osprey 2 wave power generator is 
 destroyed within one year of its installation. For purposes of this
 claim, OSPREY 2 is installed when it first begins to generate
 electricity. Destroyed is intrepreted as total destruction, sinking,
 damage sufficient to require that OSPREY 2 be returned to a drydock
 for repairs, or intentional scuttling due to damage. If the OSPREY 2
 is destroyed prior to installation or is not installed by 1/1/2000,
 this claim will be judged YES. Background: The OSPREY (Ocean Swell
 Powered Renewable Energy) is a generator that produces power from the 
 action of ocean waves. OSPREY 1 was installed off of the Scottish
 coast on 2 August 1995 with much fanfare, only to sink within weeks
 of installation. The designer claims that the basic design is sound,
 and that OSPREY 2, an exact copy, will be installed in the same area
 by the Summer of 1996. For more detail, see Nature v377 page 6.

Claim ID:      P!NP
Creation Date: 1995/08/30
Due Date:      2010/01/01

 This claim will be held true if the computational class NP
 (non-deterministic polynomially determinable) is proven to be
 distinct from P (polynomial) for some category of NP (i.e. NP-hard,
 NP-complete, etc.). This does not require proof for the full spectrum 
 of NP. A proof will be held acceptable if it has reached general
 consensus in the relevant communities (i.e. among academics in the
 area of computational complexity - Comp. Sci., Oper. Res., et.al.),
 and has received at least 10 citations in peer-review journals.

Claim ID:      PCWED
Creation Date: 1997/08/13
Due Date:      2000/01/01

 This Claim will pay 1 if by December 31, 1999, Prince Charles
 remmarries. Otherwise this claim will pay 0.

Claim ID:      PFol
Creation Date: 1995/03/27
Due Date:      2011/06/01

 
    This claim will be judged YES if by 1 Jan 2010 knowledge of a
    protein's amino acid sequence is sufficient to determine its tertiary
    structure in a given medium. Success is defined by the following
    criteria.
    
     1. At least 10 previously unknown protein tertiary structures will be
        determined from amino acid sequence. Any number of persons or
        groups may be allowed to predict structures; however, groups used
        to satisfy this claim must have a success rate of greater than
        2/3. (i.e., if the group predicts 10 structures correctly, they
        must predict no more than 5 incorrectly in the same time period.)
     2. Proteins used to satisfy this claim must meet the following
        criteria:
           + Must be nontrivial in size: greater than 50 amino acids
           + Must be nontrivial in composition: more than 8 different
             amino acid residues within the predicted structure
           + Must differ by at least 25% of amino acid sequence from known
             structures in the Brookhaven Protein Data Bank and from other
             structures previously predicted but not evaluated against
             experimental evidence
           + Must occur naturally: designed proteins are not acceptable
           + Must not consist of all alpha-helix or all beta-strand/sheet.
     3. A structure is considered correctly predicted if the average RMS
        deviation of all backbone and side-chain atoms (excluding
        hydrogens) is less than .25 Angstroms or within the error bars of
        the experimental method used to determine the structure, whichever
        is worse. Any medium is acceptable-correctly determining crystal,
        solution, or vacuum structure satisfies this claim.
     4. Correctly predicting the structure of a region within a larger
        protein is acceptable, provided the region meets the criteria in
        (2) above and the predicted region is indicated before
        experimental determination of the structure.

Claim ID:      PicF
Creation Date: 1995/01/27
Due Date:      2006/06/30

 By the end of the year 2005, 20% of US households will have
 videophones which they use at least ten times a year.

Claim ID:      PnoC
Creation Date: 1996/05/13
Due Date:      2016/11/09

 The claim will be judged TRUE if, prior to the judgement date, a
 candidate for president is accurately quoted in widely distributed
 print or electronic media during the campaign as saying that he/she
 is not a practicing Christian, AND that candidate is elected as
 president. If by the judgement date no elected candidate has made
 this statement, or the question has not been asked, the claim will be 
 judged FALSE.

Claim ID:      Popl
Creation Date: 1995/03/13
Due Date:      2051/01/01

 
    The worlds total population will reach the 10 billion mark in or
    before the year 2050. This claim shall be judged YES if the total
    world population reaches 10 billion or more in the United Nations
    Population Division's 2050 revision of World Population Prospects or
    in a revision any year earlier than that. (1994 at
    [1]gopher://gopher.undp.org:70/00/ungophers/popin/wdtrends/pop1994).
    If there is no 2050 revision of World Population Prospects, the claim
    will be judged based on other publications from the UN Population
    Division, or if necessary from similar international institutions.
 
 References
 
    1. gopher://gopher.undp.org/00/ungophers/popin/wdtrends/pop1994

Claim ID:      Pres00
Creation Date: 1998/01/21
Due Date:      2001/01/26

 
    Claim: The Republican candidate wins the November 2000 U.S.
    presidential election. _The fine print:_ For the purposes of this
    claim, the winner of the presidential election will be the winner as
    determined by the U.S. government, following the rules outlined in the
    U.S. Constitution and relevant laws (electoral college, U.S. House
    vote, etc.). Victor will be determined by the judge on January 26,
    2001, based on the official results of the election. YES coupons will
    pay $1.00 if the Republican candidate as nominated and confirmed by
    the Republican National Party is victorious. Otherwise, NO coupons
    will pay $1.00. Should the Republican Party cease to exist as of the
    November 2000 presidential election, or if it fails to produce a
    candidate for that election, this claim will be judged in favor of NO
    claims.

Claim ID:      Prim
Creation Date: 1995/09/19
Due Date:      2004/02/20

 
 The Claim
 
    By the closing date of 20th February 2004 at noon GMT a prime number
    with at least one million decimal digits will have been found. Its
    value in the form of its full decimal expansion must be made public
    before the closing date. The number must have passed a proven
    primarity test. If there is significant doubt about the validity of a
    claimed find then the claim judge may wait for up to one year after
    the closing date for the primarity to be confirmed by an independent
    team using a different computer and independently written software.
    For information on prime number records consult
      * The sci.math FAQ: Prime Numbers at
        [1]http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/sc
        i-math-faq/primes/faq.html
      * The Largest Known Prime at [2]http://www.utm.
        edu/research/primes/largest.html
      * a prime numbers ftp site at [3]ftp://ftp.ox.ac.uk/pub/math
        /primes/
 
 References
 
    1. http://www.cis.ohio-state.edu/hypertext/faq/usenet/sci-math-faq/ primes/faq.html
    2. http://www.utm.edu/research/primes/largest.html
    3. ftp://ftp.ox.ac.uk/pub/math/primes/

Claim ID:      QMUM
Creation Date: 1995/08/07
Due Date:      2000/01/01

 Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth the Queen Mother (mother of Queen
 Elizabeth II, the reigning monarch of the United Kingdom) was born in 
 1900. If she is still alive for any part of January 1st 2000, claim
 pays $1, otherwise claim pays $0.

Claim ID:      Quak
Creation Date: 1995/01/30
Due Date:      2011/06/30

 An earthquake of Richter magnitude >=8, with epicenter within 100
 miles of (one of the US states) CA,OR,WA,AZ,NV,ID will occur before
 the end of 2010.

Claim ID:      RACE
Creation Date: 1995/10/10
Due Date:      2060/01/01

 
    The US census has projected that non-Hispanic whites will become a
    minority of US citizens and permanent residents sometime in the middle
    of the 21st century. Historically, the US census figures have been
    overly conservative in estimating how fast the racial shift of
    population in the US will occur. This claim is judged "YES" if:
     1. The US census reports that the minority of the population in the
        existing 50 states and the District of Columbia are white are and
        non-Hispanic before 2060.
     2. The US census ceases to report statistics on race for any reason
        (in such a way that the white, non-Hispanic population can be
        easily discerned).
     3. The borders of the US change in such a way that some portion
        containing more than 1% of the population of the lower 48 states
        and the District of Columbia is no longer reported on by the US
        census. (Alaska and Hawaii are specifically exempted from this
        clause, i.e. if either or both of these states opt out of the US,
        the claim still stands). (The existing district of Columbia will
        be included even if it is converted to a state or other legal
        status).
        
    Each "YES" coupon plays $0.25 each decare before 2060 and after and
    including 2020 , that the US census reports a minority of the US
    population is white and non-Hispanic (or any other of the above "YES"
    criteria occur). (i.e. the census years 2020,2030,2040,2050) with the
    remainder of the credibill going to the "NO" coupon holders.

Claim ID:      RHin03
Creation Date: 1998/11/13
Due Date:      TBD

 By December 31, 2003, the Riemann Hypothesis will be proven true. The 
 Riemann Hypothesis is that the only nonreal, conplex zeroes of the
 Riemann zeta function lie on the line of all complex numbers with
 real part equal to 1/2.

Claim ID:      RHyp
Creation Date: 1995/01/31
Due Date:      2023/12/31

 The Riemann Hypothesis is "All the complex zeros of the Zeta function 
 have real part 1/2." This will be settled by the end of 2020. The
 conditions of the claim are the same as for the Goldbach Conjecture
 Claim.

Claim ID:      RO_EC
